  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain industries are typically required to report suspicious transactions or activities to designated authorities. Specific reporting obligations can vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting to financial intelligence units\n2. Filing suspicious activity reports (SARs)\n3. Maintaining transaction records\n4. Implementing know-your-customer (KYC) procedures\n5. Conducting customer due diligence\n\nSpecific requirements depend on local laws and regulations.",
